<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Budget airline Tigerair has officially shut down after 13 years in the air as coronavirus continues to wreak havoc on the travel industry. </p>

<p>The low-cost carrier, which was run by Virgin Australia, made the announcement on Thursday night.</p>

<p>'There is no denying these are tough times for everyone in the travel and tourism industry,' a spokesman said.</p>

<p>'And sadly, after nearly 13 years of operation we have made the difficult decision to discontinue the Tigerair Australia brand.'</p>

<p>Customers with Tigerair flight credit will be able to put it towards Virgin Australia flights. </p>
